{
  "stem": "4361.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So first in school-- and these are my memories-- first, they forbade-- the Hungarians forbade any one of us to speak among ourselves because the mother tongue was Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They forbade to ever use a Romanian word.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because if anybody was caught using a Romanian word, you had to pay a fine.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And by the way, it was the same thing during the Romanian schooling.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember that very well.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there, it was even a little more difficult because most of us spoke Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was our first language.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But anybody caught speaking had to pay a fine, one leu, or during the Hungarians, one pengo.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that was the first-- they-- they were after the Romanians.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then, the Romanians, most of the functionaries left town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Jews were more or less all right except in 1942, the Hungarian government issued a law which said all those Jews who do not have Hungarian citizenship-- in other words, are not native Hungarians-- or born in the city of Sighet, all those Jews who are foreigners from Poland, specifically, have to report because they are going to be resettled in Poland.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, that was a terrible thing because there were lots of Jews who were not native Hungarians or Romanians, depending on who were born there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in fact, my brother Alex, Shandor, had a girlfriend at that time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I remember her very well, a beautiful girl , [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And her parents were from Poland, who apparently never bothered to get the Hungarian citizenship in 1940.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Or maybe they-- I really don't know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But they were-- all those Jews who were considered not 'Hungarians' were taken and deported.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
